cs.NI, cs.CE, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.DB

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of IoT devices and cloud computing for real-time monitoring and data transmission.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also likely as the paper focuses on structural health monitoring, which involves computational analysis and modeling.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the software architecture of the proposed system and the technologies used for implementation.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of cloud computing for processing and visualization of monitoring results.
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper mentions the use of NoSql database for storing and processing monitoring data.
